Date: 18 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Alert Messages [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/en_urgences.htm>

Foot and mouth disease (virus type A) in Mongolia
(Date of previous outbreak of foot and mouth disease in Mongolia reported
to the OIE: February 2004).
Information received on 18 Aug 2005 from Dr Ravdan Sanjaatogtokh, Director,
State Veterinary Services, Ministry of Food and Agriculture, Ulaanbaatar:
Report date: 18 Aug 2005.
An emergency report was received from the field on 12 Aug 2005. Laboratory
diagnosis was made on 17 Aug.
Outbreak location: Bayantumen county, Dornod province, in the eastern part
of the country.
Total number of animals in the outbreak: 118 head of cattle.
No. of cases: 118 head of cattle.
Control measures:
- quarantine;
- stamping out;
- movement control;
- zoning;
- disinfection.
--
OIE Animal Health Information Department
<information.dept@oie.int>
[Further details will be published in the next issue of weekly Disease
Information, available on line as from Friday afternoon 19 Aug 2005. - Mod.PC]
